almost time for wine i got through my supermarket trip earlier  just   i decided rather than walking to our local one as i have done for 6 weeks  i would take my car to a bigger one to have more choice and be able to get more but it was awful  it was pretty quick to get in but once i was inside  it was way too busy which made it impossible to keep apart from the supermarket staff let alone the other people  i actually felt very anxious to be around so many people and i spent a fortune  i wont be doing that again but at least we will be very well stocked for a while  i even treated myself to these flowers   this afternoon i managed to move the ladders on the bunk beds by myself  with actual tools and stuff  so the room is finally finished  the star wars sheets arrived too so they have been washed and tumbled  ready for using tonight  the sheets are pretty bright and not very insta friendly but my boys really love them and that is the important thing  this afternoon we are hunkered down watching a film  it has been a long week but happy that we are all happy  safe and well  i hope you are too  periodhomesofinsta riponhouselife oldtownliving victorianhouselife victorianhome periodproperty realperiodhome periodstyle periodliving flowers quarantine weekend

have you ever felt like your heart has been on god’s surgical table and moreso now   where it seems like your thoughts and emotions have finally caught up with you    • • have you found it easy to avoid the worries  the hurts  the pains  the wounds  the bruises of your heart  through the busyness of life   but that escape place of “busyness” doesn’t seem to be at bay now and you’re finally confronted with the rawness of your heart with nowhere to hide   and it seems each day god is surfacing the compiled and hidden things you never wanted to admit to or face as you knew the pain would be too much to face • • what of if god told you  you’re in safe hands; his hands   and what you thought didn’t matter  but caused great hurt  worry  anxiety  grief and defence to your heart  is actually what he cares about most  more than the ‘works of your hands’   and he wants to have a time of openness and intimacy to discuss these things with you • • what of if the things you thought he didn’t care about are actually the things he cares most about  allow him in  • • it’s okay - he wants to stabilise the heart beat of your heart - to give you his true peace  the surgery may hurt  but it will lead to desired healing and wholeness  • • he’s got you just where he wants you allow him in  ❤️ • •  meditation hesgotyou quarantine quarantime heartsurgery pain hurt grief relief wholeness peace acceptance inspired  pensketch judahelart

quarantine skincare: 1 tbsp brown sugar  1 tspn lime juice  2 tbsp honey  although we should all be social distancing and not offering kisses to anyone at this time  it’s important that we don’t neglect our lips  let’s keep them soft and smooth  by now i’m sure you know just how much i love a good ole diy  so here’s a lip scrub diy to keep those lips soft  smooth and hydrated   mix together all the ingredients  next be sure to wash your hands  it’s quarantine season so we have to do our due diligence   after you wash your hands apply mixture to lips using your finger or a toothbrush  be sure scrub top and bottom lip 4 to 5 times then let sit for 4 to 5 minutes before wiping off with a warm cloth or paper towel   bonus: mix olive oil or avocado oil with honey to create a moisturizing lip balm  nidasii experience beauty naturally skincare sheabutter plantbasedskincare🌱 melanin selfcare wellness diy harlem nyc  skincarejunkie skincarejunkies quarantine diy scrub lipscrubs honey lime brownsugar

the sourdough chronicles  cont’d : teo happy loaves of marinated olive country bread with herbs de province and toasted sesame seeds      made two loaves that baked beautifully this little noe starter is truly a gift that keeps on giving       we initially added only half the required amount of water to the leaven  and i thought it would be a mess  fortunately  hubs then added water  based on feel and texture of the dough   which resulted in a drier but easier to handle dough baby  with each bulk fermentation  the dough became more firm and airy  but not as hydrated and sticky as the previous bakes   end result: delicious  full  airy and soft sourdough with crackling  crunchy exteriors  have to work on timing next time  so we aren’t up until 10 pm      happy mother’s day

the comfort dish of chinese food  this chicken fried rice is made in brown rice which essentially being made of whole grain is considered healthier   it has other benefits as well  that include the fiber aiding in lowering cholesterol levels and clearing of the bowel  however  its a low glycemic index food  ie  contains carbohydrates that are slower to be digested  absorbed and metabolised hence causing a lower rise in blood glucose and insulin level   ive cooked this with tossed carrots  beans  onions and chicken adding to the nutritional value   the good thing about this dish is that you can curate it with all the vegetables of your choice and irrespective of wether you love or absolutely hate the vegetable  you cannot help but relish the fried rice in all its entirety while providing your body with sufficient nutrients  it doesnt get better than this 😉

early walk round the local streets today as i had a very early call  then some pilates stretches  then started the week with a pick me up from the community that is @markshayler ‘s weekly communion   i feel better now and ready to start the week in a positive way    last night   i read a really long post by a doctor advising people to be sensible   saying that the government funded bank holiday that had gone on for weeks had to end   that we had to start dipping toes into the water   and i felt sad  these past weeks havent been a government funded bank holiday for me - in fact far from it   and there are many who are in situations worse than mine   what i feel most frustrated about is not the complexity of the decision  but how the decision has  or has not  been communicated to us   leaders  like doctors  have a responsibility to the people that they lead and look after   i understand that this is difficult   i understand that there is no clear answer  that nothing is guaranteed   i understand that things need to change  slowly  that i need to take care and be sensible   but there are ways to communicate complexity that work   ask doctors who have to explain complicated diagnoses every day   one of those doctors  one that works in a&e wrote this last night and it resonated far more for me:  there are rarely clearly “right or wrong” decisions in medicine  they often lay in shades of grey  however  the worst decision is one that patients don’t understand  don’t believe or cannot trust  i felt like that patient last night   today i’m not watching the news and it’s a bit better      quarantine quarantinewalks thestreetswhereilive fromwhereistand westhampstead lookforthelight daysofsmallthings documentyourdays

how to meditate and get your om on while smoking-in during quarantine⁠ ⁠ with everyone sheltering in place these days  a number of people have expressed that it is a time to get into meditation or back into meditation  now  it can be a bit like one of those new years resolutions — i guess we can call them covid-19 resolutions  ⁠ ⁠ to help those getting back into the practice  i thought it might be appropriate to offer some tips or some guidelines for those who might be newcomers or a little rusty ⁠ ⁠ for all the suggestions i will give  know that over the course of many years i have disregarded  ignored  or broken many of the traditional rules and principles of meditation   for that matter  i’m not very good at following most rules   the point is that if you follow the guidelines  you get better results  and your practice gets better  or goes deeper — or becomes filled with light  considering that each of us is a unique individual  naturally  you will also want to mold them into what works best for you  that’s why i call them tips  not rules ⁠ ⁠ let’s start with the ideal time to meditate  in some ways  whenever you meditate is the best time  just because you did it  nonetheless  the optimum time is early in the morning  about an hour before first light  so that you finish the meditation as the day is dawning ⁠ ⁠ link in bio⁠ ⁠ districtgardensdc dgdc membersonly meditate delivery thedopelife quarantine higherlearning meds selfcare⁠

in this realm full of self made fantasies   we all got lost in the dreams  planned a lot  thought a lot   went to a lot of routes not knowing where they led us to   have done the things   that never ever had intended to   but always ignored that world isnt a constant thing   just like a clock   it runs around us  perhaps we run after it  but the clock can stuck  so it happened   everytime is jammed now   all our dreams  and plans are gone   sitting inside my room   windows closed  curtains drawn   all my senses are panicked  all my nerves are tired of aching   my little brain isnt competent enough to analyze what exactly is going to happen  will i survive or would i die  i know  maybe sooner or may be a bit later   there would be a knock at the door   signifying that time has come   time to leave this realm   carrying buckets of our deeds we have to catch the train   there isnt any option way around   i know it will come ripping the door   so my depraved nafs is pondering over an idea   lets face it zumar  no matter what you have done   you will own your deeds  you will ask pardon   you will do your best to get the bad bucket of yours a little lower and then you will wait for the door to be knocked   and when it will  you will embrace it   with courage and a slight smile   for you will be going to the true realm the world that will belong to the good ones  where there will be no fear nor a shadow of death where there will be no boundings of time _____________________________ @zaysezumar @streetwritersofficial @globalagepoetry @inklyte @globalagecaption globalpagepoetry quarantine randomthoughts instagood instagram pakistan pakiwriters poeticjustice igdaily writersofinstagram writershub streetwritersofficial inklyte poem

latest catch up and dress up with @adoctorinadress   preakness it would’ve been race day at pimlico yesterday  but was preakness at home instead  the preakness is the second leg of the triple crown  and an excuse for us to wear our racing outfits  including this vintage frank olive hat  i borrowed it from my parents’ neighbor  mrs  judy brooking  in high school  it’s lavender and i adored it  i ended up borrowing it enough times that mrs  judy gave it to me  about twenty years after i first borrowed it  it keeps her memory alive  she passed away six years ago  i wore it with this marchesa dress as a background actor in the derby movie 50 to 1  lots of good memories here 🍹🍹🍹 most people know that the official cocktail of derby is the mint julep  but did you know the black-eyed susan is the preakness’ cocktail combine one ounce makers mark bourbon whiskey  one ounce dekuyper peachtree schnapps  one ounce effen vodka  two ounces of orange juice  and two ounces of sour mix  shake  then garnish with an orange wheel and a cherry  for the mocktail version  combine two ounces orange juice  two ounces of sour mix  a tablespoon of peach purée  then top with club soda to taste  🍹🍹🍹 preakness horseracing alonetogether quarantine quarantineandchill girlfriends friends cocktail cocktails weekend 1stpreaknessathome quarantinelife pimlico maryland 1stbet

lasagne from scratch👩🏻‍🍳       serves 2   lasagne sheets 250g 5% fat beef mince tin of chopped tomatoes  200ml red wine 2tbsp tomato purée 1tbsp ketchup  1 carrot  1 onion 3 cloves garlic couple of mushrooms  salt  pepper olive oil tomato sauce:  on a medium-high heat gently fry the onions & carrots  once softened add crushed garlic & mushrooms  after a few minutes add in the beef and brown  add the tomato purée & 100ml of wine and gently simmer  then add the chopped tomatoes  after a few minutes pour in the rest of the wine & 1tbsp ketchup  turn the heat down to low & leave to simmer until it thickens  white sauce: 50g butter 50g flour  500ml milk parmesan  the amount you put in is down to your taste  in a saucepan over a low-medium heat melt the butter & then stir in the flour to create a paste  cook for 2minutes  then slowly add bit by bit the milk  stirring continuously  the paste will eventually turn into a sauce  then finally add the cheese  in a dish  assemble your lasagne  meat  pasta  white sauce  & then repeat  cover the top in extra cheese bake in the oven for 25mins at 180c or until golden 😋       to make pasta: 100g flour  1 large egg  mix together until fully combined  knead for 5mins  leave to rest in the fridge for a minimum of 30mins  roll out & cut to shape        use plant based alternatives to make vegan veggie          helskitchen kitchen chef baker quarantinecooking cooking bakinginisolation lockdown quarantine lasagne italian pasta homecooking homemade meat cheese foodporn heartymeal comfortfood

fruit ‘n’ nut flapjack •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• who wants a crumbly flapjack no siree naaat me 😬  well then  i suggest you follow this recipe this is a recipe from my mum  and it is deeeelicous 👌🏼 •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• ingredients:  1️⃣ 175g of vegan butter  2️⃣ 140g golden syrup  3️⃣ 50g light muscovado sugar  4️⃣ 225g rolled oats  5️⃣ 25g of dried fruit and nuts from your wildest thoughts and dreams   6️⃣ 1 2 tsp of ground ginger  you can add more if you like & or other spices like cinnamon  •••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••• method:  1️⃣ heat your oven to 180 degrees c 🔥 🔥 🔥 & line a 9” tin with baking paper  2️⃣ melt butter  sugar & syrup together in a pan on a low heat  mix together  3️⃣ you can now add & mix in your oats  ground ginger powder nuts & seeds  once mixed  place in the lined baking tin & spread out and firm down   4️⃣ bake for 20-25 minutes 5️⃣ remove from oven & keep in tray  after 5minutes of cooling  mark into pieces es with a sharp knife  do not attempt to remove pieces  leave to cool down fully  i put mine in the fridge  before removing pieces from tin   6️⃣ time to enjoy

i moved to mumbai when i was 9 years old  i had been to the city a few times before and i had never seen a city as magical as this one  i was over-excited to move in here  spending evenings at marine drive  watching a movie at regal theater  seeing people from all parts of the world shop and dine around causeway  every small thing about mumbai surprised me  after a few years i got used to it and also i didnt travel much beyond my school and the town before i started my job here  after i started working in mumbai and started traveling in the local trains  buses  taxis it was a new world to me altogether  i got to witness a pool of people arriving in the city  clicking pictures outside the cst station  video calling their loved ones  and showing them the gateway  marine drive  chowpatty  and whatnot  i have heard hundreds of stories in the local train and during casual chats with my taxi driver  last week when i traveled through the empty streets of mumbai it was disheartening to see the empty streets and for the first time  there were no stories  the city where every day a sea of people arrived is now crippled by a virus but i also know that the city will fight this virus and will be back to its job of fulfilling dreams of million and being a mayanagari that it is            mumbai sea photooftheday _soi quarantine travelphotography  landscapephotography kalaajaurkal indianphotography  wanderlust travel lonelyplanetindia picoftheday indiaphotosociety ngtindia incredibleindia phonephotography indiaview theindianroute indiaclicks _woi thefleetingstar cntgiveitashot teampixel lonelyplanetindia epic mymumbai _soimumbai

📍1650s  tay  also in early spellings thea  tey  tee and at first pronounced so as to rhyme with obey; the modern pronunciation predominates from mid-18c  but earlier in english as chaa  1590s   also cha  tcha  chia  cia  the two forms of the word reflect two paths of transmission: chaa is from portuguese cha  attested in portuguese from 1550s  via macao  from mandarin  chinese  cha  cf chai   the later form  which became modern english tea  is via dutch  from malay teh and directly from chinese  amoy dialect  te  which corresponds to mandarin cha  📍the distribution of the different forms of the word in europe reflects the spread of use of the beverage  the modern english form  along with french thé  spanish te  german tee  etc   derive via dutch thee from the amoy form  reflecting the role of the dutch as the chief importers of the leaves  through the dutch east india company  from 1610   meanwhile  russian chai  persian cha  greek tsai  arabic shay  and turkish çay all came overland from the mandarin form  📍first known in paris 1635  the practice of drinking tea was first introduced to england 1644  meaning afternoon meal at which tea is served is from 1738  slang meaning marijuana 💚 which sometimes was brewed in hot water  is attested from 1935  felt as obsolete by late 1960s  tea ball is from 1895

i was safe in the french countryside for 9 weeks  and took as many precautions as i could travelling home last week; i was made to use a biometric passport machine at the gare du nord for the british passport control  they do it in france  rather than st pancras for some reason  you literally go through two passport controls back to back   which meant taking off glasses  mask and using something that wasn’t been wiped down between uses  social distancing once through passport control was utterly non-existant and it was shambolic  no advice on arrival in the uk  no tests  no temperature checks  no hand sanitizer  i decided to quarantine for 14 days anyway  just to be safe    within 9 days  i was ill  and displaying enough relevant symptoms that the tracker app i’m using asked me to apply for a test  it arrived today  i am tired  i’m still not really using social media  fb being the main exception  but i wanted to come on here and let you know that i’m safe  i’m mentally doing a lot better than i was  but i am definitely ill with -something- and i just wanted to say to you all  please  please don’t look to your government and their advisors for good examples  the virus is still here  very much so  very much still infecting and killing hundreds every day  be safe  be sensible  do the right thing  stayhome staysafe selfisolate selfisolation fuckthetories covid_19 covid19 coronavirus protectyourself protectthenhs quarantine quarantinelife covid19test stayathome mentalhealth fuckthegovernment boristhebutcher rest recover recuperate washyourhands lockdown lockdownlife lockdown2020

brothers  let’s talk about under our eyes for a second   ⁣ ⁣ i know you all work hard but we shouldn’t have to wear all our hard work and stress on our faces⁣ ⁣ the skin around our eyes is much thinner and delicate than in other places which means it’s the first place that wrinkles  fine lines  saggy skin and other signs of ageing begin to appear ⁣ ⁣ so as you exert yourself through the day you might not even realise how much the skin in this area is working; all the blinking  squinting and even laughter can contribute ⁣ ⁣ so what does this mean⁣ ⁣ it means that sometimes the skin our eyes needs a little extra attention ⁣ ⁣ in our next post we’ll share some tips for you all ⁣ ⁣ stay tuned 🤝⁣ ⁣ boomerang credit: @alexcardoso⁣ ⁣ follow @selfcarebrotherhood⁣⁣ follow @selfcarebrotherhood⁣⁣ follow @selfcarebrotherhood ⁣⁣ ⁣⁣ •⁣⁣ •⁣⁣ •⁣⁣ •⁣⁣ •⁣⁣ •⁣⁣ ⁣ ⁣ skincarejunkie skinhealth menskin⁣ mensskin skincareritual skincaretip⁣ skinproducts skincareguru skincaredaily menscare menwhomask facemask sheetmask skincare skincareman diyskincare⁣ stayhome quarantine twitter dailycleanse brotherhood selfcare diyskincare influencer manbeauty malebeauty beardboy mensfashion beauty skincareroutine

facetime photoshoot 1 x @misaaal_    the first time @misaaal_ and i spoke was super funny  i believe she found me from one of my comments on one of iraj’s videos  @alifsay   her first message to me was  “what are you” followed by “sorry i’m so hyper”  i thought to myself  “nice  what is this crackhead energy” and we instantly clicked pun definitely not intended   not something that happens too often - meeting people on the same wavelength of idiocy  but i’m glad to have known this one for as long as i have   this facetime shoot was quite a breeze  we ended up laughing and cracking stupid jokes more than we did taking photos but i’m quite happy with the way these photos turned out   working with 1 megapixel jpegs in lightroom was quite the experience after being so used to editing 24 megapixel raw files  but that’s part of the challenge involved that made this whole experience so worth it
